But I'll send you a tape of four hour live coverage of a car chase in LA -- it's not hard to get, since we get that coverage at least once a week -- and hear your defense of it. It's not Monday morning quarterbacking to say that local TV news is getting more and more sensationalistic and doesn't devote as much attention to stories that don't have compelling images (shit on fire, kids, kids on fire, what have you). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uravendawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RavenDawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/19/02 1:12:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1629.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Media Bias</span><hr size=1> Psst.... Zinj dont hate someone because they got a better straw when chosing whose womb to go into. People are not given the same chances when born as others. Some have silver spoons and some dont BUT, each has the ability to control his or her destiny.<br>
